The selectivity and disruption hypotheses for immigrant fertility
Generational convergence: first-generation fertility advantage and second-generation attenuation
Segmented assimilation (Portes & Zhou, 1993): why the linear model is insufficient
Evidence for convergence: Parrado & Morgan (2008); Parrado (2011); Hill & Johnson (2004)
