2.4 Hypotheses

H1 (Compositional): A substantial portion of the Hispanic-White childlessness gap is attributable to nativity composition, with first-generation Hispanic women having significantly lower childlessness than native-born Hispanic women.
H2 (Null for Black): The Black-White childlessness gap is not explained by nativity, given the predominantly native-born composition of the Black population.
H3 (Mediation): The foreign-born fertility advantage is mediated by marriage and religious affiliation rather than operating through an unmeasured cultural residual.
H4 (Financial): Childlessness is associated with the composition of the household balance sheet — particularly retirement assets and credit constraints — not aggregate income or wealth.
H5 (Parenthood and Debt): The transition to parenthood is the strongest demographic predictor of credit card indebtedness, consistent with the liquidity strain theory of parental debt.


